Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.94,0:19:20.42,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,除非要跟別人上床\N{\rOriginal Text}Mm. ...unless I'm getting laid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.55,0:19:22.94,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我想這應該不會發生\N{\rOriginal Text}Mm. I guess... I guess that's not on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.07,0:19:25.94,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你是怎麼到這兒的啊 瑪德琳·馬特洛克\N{\rOriginal Text}Where did you come from, Madeline Matlock?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.07,0:19:27.86,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,最開始是佛羅里達的那不勒斯\N{\rOriginal Text}Naples, Florida, originally,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.99,0:19:29.51,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,後來去佐治亞繞了一圈\N{\rOriginal Text}then a little detour through Georgia
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.64,0:19:31.56,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,再被我前夫拖去了北方\N{\rOriginal Text}before my ex-husband dragged me up north.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.69,0:19:33.08,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不是說因此 我才變得很苦很窮\N{\rOriginal Text}Not that I'm bitter and broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.21,0:19:34.91,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你是專門\N{\rOriginal Text}You specialize
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.04,0:19:36.47,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,打藥品官司的 對吧\N{\rOriginal Text}in pharmaceuticals, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.61,0:19:38.74,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我也想往這方面發展\N{\rOriginal Text}Mm-hmm. That's where I need to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.87,0:19:40.48,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你孩子們多大了\N{\rOriginal Text}How old are your kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.61,0:19:42.83,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,雙胞胎 都是八歲\N{\rOriginal Text}Uh, twins. They're eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.96,0:19:44.35,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,正是好年紀 是啊\N{\rOriginal Text}Aw. That's a great age. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.48,0:19:47.49,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,12歲就難帶了 我現在在帶我孫子\N{\rOriginal Text}12 is tougher. I'm raising my grandson...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.62,0:19:49.23,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,別找我問建議\N{\rOriginal Text}but don't ask me for any advice--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.36,0:19:50.88,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他可討厭我了\N{\rOriginal Text}he loathes me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.01,0:19:53.67,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你感恩節週末有什麼安排嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Have you got any plans for Thanksgiving weekend?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.80,0:19:56.23,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,奧林匹亞說\N{\rOriginal Text}Because Olympia mentioned
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.36,0:19:58.98,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,她想帶雙胞胎出去玩玩\N{\rOriginal Text}she'd love to take the twins on a little getaway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.11,0:20:01.28,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,當然是你們共進晚餐之後了\N{\rOriginal Text}After you all have dinner together, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.41,0:20:04.55,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,而且放個假 對大家都有好處\N{\rOriginal Text}And vacations do benefit everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.98,0:20:10.20,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,奧林園亞讓你來的 管我要週末陪護權\N{\rOriginal Text}Did Olympia send you? To ask for my weekend?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.33,0:20:12.21,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,然後朱利安解釋說\N{\rOriginal Text}And so then Julian explained that he'd be
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.34,0:20:14.51,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,如果你願意一個月內搬出婚房\N{\rOriginal Text}more than happy to let you have his weekend
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.64,0:20:16.78,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,並把房契轉讓給他\N{\rOriginal Text}if you leave the marital apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.91,0:20:19.17,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他很樂意讓你那個週末\N{\rOriginal Text}within the month and cede the deed to him
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.30,0:20:21.74,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,帶孩子 那麼 成交不\N{\rOriginal Text}in pleno. So? Do we have a deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.87,0:20:24.13,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,荒唐 你根本沒安排\N{\rOriginal Text}You're being ridiculous. You don't have plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.26,0:20:25.52,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我還真有哦\N{\rOriginal Text}Oh, as a matter of fact, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.65,0:20:27.13,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我荒唐\N{\rOriginal Text}And I'm the one being ridiculous?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.26,0:20:29.31,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不好意思 能讓我倆單獨談談嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm sorry. Uh, will you excuse us?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.44,0:20:31.09,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,沒問題\N{\rOriginal Text}Oh, you bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.27,0:20:36.75,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,荒唐的是 你竟然派馬特洛克幫你於這種骯髒事\N{\rOriginal Text}Ridiculous is sending Matlock to do your dirty work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.88,0:20:38.19,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我想著 她也許能說服你\N{\rOriginal Text}I thought she'd have more luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.32,0:20:39.89,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,看你還挺喜歡她的\N{\rOriginal Text}You seemed to like her in the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.02,0:20:41.58,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你生氣是因為我在會上打壓你\N{\rOriginal Text}You're pissed because I undercut you in the meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.71,0:20:43.06,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,是因為你針對我\N{\rOriginal Text}Yeah, because it was personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.19,0:20:44.37,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,才不是 我只是覺得你\N{\rOriginal Text}That's not true. I don't think you're acting
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.50,0:20:45.98,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,沒為律所著想\N{\rOriginal Text}in the firm's best interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.11,0:20:47.59,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你大可以發郵件給我啊 而不是\N{\rOriginal Text}Well, you could have emailed me rather than going
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.72,0:20:49.11,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,當眾針對我 是\N{\rOriginal Text}after me in public. Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.24,0:20:51.77,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不好意思 打斷一下 有麻煩了\N{\rOriginal Text}Sorry to interrupt, but we have a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.90,0:20:53.16,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,看下《郵報》\N{\rOriginal Text}Check the Post.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.03,0:20:56.73,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,哈里斯案即將開庭之際 一項研究顯示\N{\rOriginal Text}"On the eve of the Harris trial, a study reveals
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.86,0:20:58.51,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,90年代末的警察腐敗現象\N{\rOriginal Text}"police corruption in the late '90s
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.64,0:21:01.30,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,並不像最初報道的那樣普遍\N{\rOriginal Text}not as widespread as initially reported"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.43,0:21:02.73,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,什麼 而且不僅僅是《郵報》\N{\rOriginal Text}What? -And it's not just the Post.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.87,0:21:04.52,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,其他媒體也在跟進\N{\rOriginal Text}All the other outlets are picking it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.65,0:21:06.52,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,好吧 呃\N{\rOriginal Text}Okay, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.65,0:21:08.35,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你可以走了 我們稍後再談\N{\rOriginal Text}You could go, we'll talk later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.48,0:21:09.79,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我哪兒都不去\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm not going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.92,0:21:11.35,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,制定下策略吧\N{\rOriginal Text}Let's strategize.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.48,0:21:13.62,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,為了律所利益\N{\rOriginal Text}For the good of the firm?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.62,0:21:16.23,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,警察工會肯定知道\N{\rOriginal Text}Policemen's union must have known
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.36,0:21:17.79,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,會發這篇文章\N{\rOriginal Text}this article was coming out,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.92,0:21:19.75,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所以他們才降價了 沒錯\N{\rOriginal Text}and that's why they dropped the number. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.88,0:21:21.58,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,顯然是他們精心策劃的\N{\rOriginal Text}They orchestrated this, clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.71,0:21:24.15,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,特意趕在開庭前一晚 放出這篇文章\N{\rOriginal Text}And held on to the article for the night before the trial
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.28,0:21:26.89,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,目的就是盡最大可能 影響陪審團\N{\rOriginal Text}so they could inflict the most prejudice on the jury.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.02,0:21:28.63,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我整個案件都基於\N{\rOriginal Text}My entire case is based
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.76,0:21:30.15,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,警察腐敗\N{\rOriginal Text}on police corruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.28,0:21:32.33,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,該死 希望你那個毒販\N{\rOriginal Text}Damn it! Let's hope your dealer remembers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.46,0:21:34.77,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,還能記得26年前 那個吸毒的妓女\N{\rOriginal Text}a drug-addicted prostitute from 26 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.90,0:21:35.81,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你有計劃嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}You have a plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.94,0:21:36.77,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,讓他張嘴說話\N{\rOriginal Text}To get him to talk to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.90,0:21:38.94,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,當然有\N{\rOriginal Text}We sure do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.38,0:21:44.30,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們有計劃嗎 還沒有\N{\rOriginal Text}Do we have a plan? Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.43,0:21:47.04,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但我們有一整晚時間想辦法\N{\rOriginal Text}We've got all night to come up with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.13,0:21:55.13,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,記住 霍博肯 布倫達\N{\rOriginal Text}Now remember, Hoboken, Brenda,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.27,0:21:56.75,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,弗羅裏達的第一浸信會教堂\N{\rOriginal Text}First Baptist Church, Florida.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.88,0:21:58.40,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,研究的特別到位 莎拉\N{\rOriginal Text}Excellent research, Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.53,0:22:00.58,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,相當棒\N{\rOriginal Text}Really top-notch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.36,0:22:06.97,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我不認識\N{\rOriginal Text}Uh, I don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.10,0:22:08.41,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這些人 文森特·德盧卡\N{\rOriginal Text}these people. Vincent De Luca,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.54,0:22:10.54,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,回頭我跟你媽告狀去\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm gonna tell your mother you said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.67,0:22:12.02,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你認識我媽\N{\rOriginal Text}You know my mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.15,0:22:14.46,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,是我呀 瑪蒂\N{\rOriginal Text}It's me. Matty.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.59,0:22:16.90,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我搬去霍博肯的時候\N{\rOriginal Text}I met your mom when I moved
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.03,0:22:18.81,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,認識的你媽\N{\rOriginal Text}up north to Hoboken.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.94,0:22:20.38,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,開托兒所\N{\rOriginal Text}Ran day care.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.51,0:22:22.86,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,第一浸信會 跟你布倫達姑姑一起辦的\N{\rOriginal Text}First Baptist? With your Aunt Brenda?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.86,0:22:26.73,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不好意思\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.86,0:22:28.34,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我一激動就會\N{\rOriginal Text}My emphysema flares up
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.47,0:22:29.91,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,肺氣腫發作\N{\rOriginal Text}when I, when I get upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.04,0:22:31.35,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不怪你\N{\rOriginal Text}It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.48,0:22:33.04,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,只是我生病之後\N{\rOriginal Text}I guess I just look different
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.17,0:22:34.61,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,變化很大\N{\rOriginal Text}since I got sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.74,0:22:37.31,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,瘦了很多\N{\rOriginal Text}Lost a lot of weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.44,0:22:41.40,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我只是沒想到 你竟然認不出我\N{\rOriginal Text}I just never thought you wouldn't recognize me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.49,0:22:43.92,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不是 只是需要點時間想一下\N{\rOriginal Text}No, it just took a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.05,0:22:45.45,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我認出你了\N{\rOriginal Text}I-I recognize you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.58,0:22:47.67,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我剛開玩笑的 謝天謝地\N{\rOriginal Text}I was just kidding around. -Thank God.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.80,0:22:50.36,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我剛還突然緊張了一下 以為自己會在這些\N{\rOriginal Text}'Cause I suddenly panicked that I'd look nuts
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.49,0:22:51.97,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,律師面前 看起來像個瘋婆子\N{\rOriginal Text}in front of these lawyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.10,0:22:53.02,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他們去家裏那邊\N{\rOriginal Text}They came to the neighborhood
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.15,0:22:54.41,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,找你媽\N{\rOriginal Text}looking for your mom,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.54,0:22:56.85,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我跟他們說 辛迪搬去佛羅里達了\N{\rOriginal Text}and I told them, "Cindy moved to Florida.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.98,0:23:00.37,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,有什麼事呀 然後我們就來這兒了\N{\rOriginal Text}And how can I help?" And here we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.50,0:23:04.07,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他們今天好像有個大案子要開庭\N{\rOriginal Text}I think they got some big trial starting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.20,0:23:06.08,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,首先 鑒於昨晚發佈的那篇\N{\rOriginal Text}First, I'll make a motion in limine
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.21,0:23:07.60,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,帶有偏見的文章\N{\rOriginal Text}to try to get the location moved...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.73,0:23:09.30,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我會提出建議\N{\rOriginal Text}In light of the highly prejudicial article
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.43,0:23:11.39,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,改變庭審地點 兩個月前 你還說\N{\rOriginal Text}that came out last night. Two months ago, you argued
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.52,0:23:13.52,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,陪審團能應對這些報道呢\N{\rOriginal Text}the jury could handle the publicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.65,0:23:15.91,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不可能成功 但我們得把這事記錄在案 以備上訴用\N{\rOriginal Text}It won't work, but we need it on record for appeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.04,0:23:17.52,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,開庭時 駁回陪審團坐定後\N{\rOriginal Text}Motion denied. After the jury is seated,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.65,0:23:19.52,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,會進入到開庭陳詞\N{\rOriginal Text}we'll move into opening arguments.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.65,0:23:21.96,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那是我第一次講述你故事的機會\N{\rOriginal Text}That's my first chance to tell your story.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.09,0:23:23.57,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這是個恐怖故事\N{\rOriginal Text}And it's a horror story.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.70,0:23:26.44,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,雷蒙德·哈里斯在方寸牢籠裏\N{\rOriginal Text}Raymond Harris spent 26 years
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.57,0:23:30.14,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,待了26年 明知自己是無辜的\N{\rOriginal Text}in a six-by-nine cell, knowing he was innocent
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.27,0:23:31.45,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但也知道\N{\rOriginal Text}but also knowing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.58,0:23:32.84,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,無人在意\N{\rOriginal Text}that no one cared.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.97,0:23:35.89,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但你們可以讓他知道 你們在乎\N{\rOriginal Text}But you can show him that you care.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.02,0:23:37.76,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那時我會解釋\N{\rOriginal Text}And that's when I'll try to get in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.89,0:23:41.33,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你不出庭作證的原因\N{\rOriginal Text}an explanation for the reason you're not taking the stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.46,0:23:44.68,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你們可以讓他知道 你們關心他的創傷\N{\rOriginal Text}You can show him that you care about his trauma.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.81,0:23:47.42,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,到現在他還無法入睡\N{\rOriginal Text}The fact that he still can't sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.55,0:23:49.73,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,害怕在公眾面前說話\N{\rOriginal Text}He has a crippling fear of public speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.86,0:23:52.25,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,反對 反對我開庭陳詞\N{\rOriginal Text}Objection. During my opening statement?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.38,0:23:53.47,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,上前說話\N{\rOriginal Text}Approach the bench.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.73,0:23:57.69,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,她顯然是在暗示她的委託人\N{\rOriginal Text}She's clearly trying to imply that her client
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.82,0:23:59.43,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,之所以沒出庭 是因為受到了精神創傷\N{\rOriginal Text}isn't testifying because he's been traumatized,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.56,0:24:01.04,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們都知道 真實原因是\N{\rOriginal Text}when we know for a fact that it's because
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.17,0:24:02.74,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,她不希望他前科被拎出來講\N{\rOriginal Text}she doesn't want his priors brought up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.87,0:24:03.74,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這次我還是\N{\rOriginal Text}Again,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.87,0:24:04.96,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,會失敗\N{\rOriginal Text}I'll lose,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.09,0:24:07.40,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但我得讓陪審團記住這點\N{\rOriginal Text}but we'll get it in the jury's heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.53,0:24:09.14,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,抱歉 法官大人\N{\rOriginal Text}Apologies, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.27,0:24:10.53,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我會更加小心用詞的\N{\rOriginal Text}I will be more careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.06,0:24:18.45,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,26年前 一個吸毒的妓女\N{\rOriginal Text}Look, there's just no way that I'm gonna remember a...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.58,0:24:20.76,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我怎麼可能記得住\N{\rOriginal Text}lady-of-the-night junkie from 26 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.89,0:24:21.93,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我懂腦子\N{\rOriginal Text}Oh, I know how tricky
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.06,0:24:23.24,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,有多難記事\N{\rOriginal Text}memory can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.37,0:24:24.89,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我把美國老年人協會建議的\N{\rOriginal Text}And I do all those exercises
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.02,0:24:26.55,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所有練習都做過\N{\rOriginal Text}that the AARP suggests,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.68,0:24:29.94,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,可我發現 所有能觸發記憶的 往往都是具體細節\N{\rOriginal Text}but I find what triggers my memory are specifics.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.07,0:24:31.64,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你有什麼具體細節嗎 馬丁內斯先生\N{\rOriginal Text}You got any, Mr. Martinez?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.77,0:24:33.29,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,當然有\N{\rOriginal Text}Yeah, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.42,0:24:35.86,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,有些事 也許能幫你回憶起1996年的事\N{\rOriginal Text}Here's what we can tell you to help you recall 1996.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.99,0:24:38.04,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那年是選舉年 克林頓第二個任期\N{\rOriginal Text}It was an election year. Clinton's second term.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.17,0:24:39.39,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,對手是鮑勃·多爾\N{\rOriginal Text}Bob Dole was his opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.35,0:24:44.83,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,出現了第一個被克隆的哺乳動物綿羊 多莉\N{\rOriginal Text}Dolly the sheep was the first mammal to be cloned.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.96,0:24:45.74,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那可是大事\N{\rOriginal Text}That was a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.87,0:24:47.26,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,還有麥卡雷納舞\N{\rOriginal Text}Macarena.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.39,0:24:49.35,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所有人都在跳麥卡雷納舞\N{\rOriginal Text}Everyone was doing the Macarena.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.48,0:24:51.27,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我可沒跳 其他人跳\N{\rOriginal Text}I wasn't doing the Macarena. Other people were,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.40,0:24:52.79,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但我記得 當時有想過 幸好我不配槍\N{\rOriginal Text}and I remember thinking it's a good thing I don't carry,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.92,0:24:54.44,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,要不然我真會把他們腦袋崩了的\N{\rOriginal Text}'cause I would've blown their brains out.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.58,0:24:56.05,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,研究的很到位\N{\rOriginal Text}That's great research.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.19,0:24:59.10,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但是維尼 我想你回想一下\N{\rOriginal Text}But, Vinnie, I want you to cast your mind back
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.23,0:25:01.84,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,麥卡雷納搞得你很生氣的那段時光\N{\rOriginal Text}to the time when the Macarena was making you angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.67,0:25:09.15,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,好吧 我記得有個紅頭髮的癮君子\N{\rOriginal Text}Okay, look, I do remember this one redhead junkie
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.29,0:25:10.98,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,有天突然就消失了\N{\rOriginal Text}who just up and disappeared one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.11,0:25:12.55,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,可能就是她\N{\rOriginal Text}And that could be her.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.68,0:25:13.99,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不是卡拉 知道了\N{\rOriginal Text}Not Carla. -Got it,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.12,0:25:15.47,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你記得她叫什麼嗎 不是 我當初就\N{\rOriginal Text}but do you remember her name? No, that's what
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.60,0:25:16.99,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這麼叫她的 不是卡拉\N{\rOriginal Text}I used to called her: "Not Carla."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.12,0:25:17.99,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那會兒我很喜歡電視劇《乾杯酒吧》\N{\rOriginal Text}See, I used to love the TV show Cheers.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.12,0:25:19.30,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你還記得那部劇嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Do you remember that show?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.43,0:25:20.43,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,記得 但這些年輕人應該不知道\N{\rOriginal Text}I do, but I'm guessing these kids don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.56,0:25:22.21,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,是 也許吧\N{\rOriginal Text}Yeah, probably not.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.34,0:25:24.00,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,反正 每次我一說 乾杯卡拉\N{\rOriginal Text}Anyway, I'd say "Cheers, Carla,"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.13,0:25:25.56,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,她就會很生氣 說她不叫卡拉\N{\rOriginal Text}and she'd get all pissed off and say that's not her name.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.69,0:25:27.48,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,隨便啦 反正也差不多\N{\rOriginal Text}Whatever, it was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.61,0:25:29.39,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,最後我就叫她 不是卡拉\N{\rOriginal Text}Eventually, I just called her Not Carla.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.52,0:25:32.61,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但跟卡拉很接近 對吧 卡莉 卡羅琳 卡羅萊娜\N{\rOriginal Text}But it's like Carla, right? Carly? Caroline? Carolina?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.74,0:25:33.83,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,卡爾琳娜 卡洛塔 卡琳\N{\rOriginal Text}Carlina, Carlotta, Carlin...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.96,0:25:35.75,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,卡琳 是了\N{\rOriginal Text}Carlin. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.53,0:25:40.40,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,好 駕照是1993到1998年間\N{\rOriginal Text}Okay, driver's license 1993 to 1998,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.53,0:25:43.84,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,名字是卡琳 拼寫是 卡 王 雙 木 林\N{\rOriginal Text}first name Carlin, spelled I-N, E-N, O-N, Y-N,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.97,0:25:45.80,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,年齡18到32歲之間\N{\rOriginal Text}ages 18 to 32.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.93,0:25:46.93,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那就廣撒網吧\N{\rOriginal Text}Might as well cast a wide net.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.06,0:25:48.41,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,是 可這範圍是真的大\N{\rOriginal Text}Yeah, well, that's very wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.54,0:25:49.54,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,可能要花太多時間\N{\rOriginal Text}I mean, that might take too long...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.67,0:25:51.20,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,好 214個結果\N{\rOriginal Text}Okay. 214 hits.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.33,0:25:52.68,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,現在速度快多了 瑪蒂\N{\rOriginal Text}Things are faster now, Matty.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.81,0:25:54.16,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,比利 把他們生活拼湊起來\N{\rOriginal Text}Billy, let's piece together their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.29,0:25:56.03,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,排除所有1996年不在本州的人\N{\rOriginal Text}Eliminate anyone who was out of state in 1996.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.16,0:25:58.29,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,要找紅頭髮\N{\rOriginal Text}We are looking for redheads, people.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.95,0:26:03.43,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,福格森警探\N{\rOriginal Text}Detective Ferguson,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.56,0:26:05.25,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,雷蒙德·哈里斯跟你和你同事們說過多少次\N{\rOriginal Text}how many times did Raymond Harris tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.38,0:26:07.74,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他是無辜的\N{\rOriginal Text}and your fellow officers that he was innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.87,0:26:09.30,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不清楚\N{\rOriginal Text}I have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.43,0:26:10.78,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,給個大概數值 能有超過100次嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Approximately. More than 100?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.91,0:26:13.35,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,反對 自問自答\N{\rOriginal Text}Objection. Asked and answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.48,0:26:14.87,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,法官大人 我想建立行為模式\N{\rOriginal Text}Your Honor, I'm trying to establish a course of conduct.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.44,0:26:17.92,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,允許\N{\rOriginal Text}I'll allow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.05,0:26:19.62,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,謝謝你認為\N{\rOriginal Text}Thank you. Is it your best estimate
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.75,0:26:22.40,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他自稱無罪的次數 超過100次了嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}that he said he was not guilty more than 100 times?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.53,0:26:24.14,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,也許吧 好的\N{\rOriginal Text}Probably. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.27,0:26:27.80,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所以 雷蒙德·哈里斯說過一百多次 他是無罪的\N{\rOriginal Text}So, more than 100 times Mr. Harris says he's not guilty,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.93,0:26:29.45,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但在你審問他11個小時候\N{\rOriginal Text}and after you question him for 11 hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.58,0:26:30.89,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他說自己有罪了\N{\rOriginal Text}he says he's guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.02,0:26:32.63,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,雷蒙德認罪多久後\N{\rOriginal Text}How long after Raymond confessed
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.76,0:26:33.89,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,翻供的\N{\rOriginal Text}did he retract that confession?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.02,0:26:35.76,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,大概十分鐘後吧\N{\rOriginal Text}About ten minutes later.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.89,0:26:37.81,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,八分鐘 這期間他做了什麼\N{\rOriginal Text}Eight. What did he do in between?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.94,0:26:38.94,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,記不清了\N{\rOriginal Text}I can't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.07,0:26:40.29,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他去洗手間了\N{\rOriginal Text}He went to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.42,0:26:42.33,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,福格森警探 雷蒙德撤回\N{\rOriginal Text}Detective Ferguson, after Raymond
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.47,0:26:44.99,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,認罪供詞後 你們做進一步調查了嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}retracted his confession, did you investigate further?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.12,0:26:47.21,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,沒有 除了被一位承認自己\N{\rOriginal Text}No. Was there anything to link Mr. Harris
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.34,0:26:48.86,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,醉酒的目擊者 看到他出現在案發現場之外\N{\rOriginal Text}to the crime scene other than the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.99,0:26:50.78,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,還有其他任何能將哈里斯和\N{\rOriginal Text}that he was seen in the area by one eyewitness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.91,0:26:52.78,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,案發現場聯繫起來的證據嗎 有的\N{\rOriginal Text}who was admittedly intoxicated? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.91,0:26:54.87,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他符合我們做出的兇手描述\N{\rOriginal Text}He matched the description we put out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.00,0:26:57.44,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,沒錯 這描述我也有\N{\rOriginal Text}Right. I have that description.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.57,0:27:00.83,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,將此作為原告證物 4B\N{\rOriginal Text}Admitting this in evidence as plaintiff exhibit 4B.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.96,0:27:02.49,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,能大聲讀一下嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Can you read it aloud, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.62,0:27:04.66,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,黑人男性 無面部鬍鬚\N{\rOriginal Text}Black male, no facial hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.79,0:27:06.71,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,身高在五英尺十到六英尺之間\N{\rOriginal Text}Five-foot-ten to six-foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.84,0:27:08.53,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,當然\N{\rOriginal Text}Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.67,0:27:10.19,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我能理解你為什麼會認為\N{\rOriginal Text}I can see why you thought
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.32,0:27:11.63,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,是雷蒙德·哈里斯\N{\rOriginal Text}it was Raymond Harris.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.76,0:27:13.24,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,沒有更多問題了 法官大人\N{\rOriginal Text}No more questions, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.37,0:27:15.76,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,再次感謝你為國效力\N{\rOriginal Text}Thank you again for your service.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.89,0:27:18.63,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們從最後一點開始吧 福格森警探\N{\rOriginal Text}Let's start at that last point, Detective Ferguson.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.76,0:27:20.33,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,為什麼哈里斯撤回認罪後\N{\rOriginal Text}Why didn't you investigate further
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.46,0:27:22.81,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你沒有做進一步調查\N{\rOriginal Text}after Mr. Harris retracted his confession?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.94,0:27:25.42,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,因為撤回認罪很常見\N{\rOriginal Text}Because people take back confessions all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.55,0:27:27.64,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們沒繼續調查的原因很簡單\N{\rOriginal Text}The reason we didn't keep looking is simple:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.77,0:27:31.34,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,最可信的解釋 通常就是\N{\rOriginal Text}the most believable explanation for what happened
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.47,0:27:33.12,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,事情的真相\N{\rOriginal Text}is usually what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.26,0:27:34.43,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所以 在你看來\N{\rOriginal Text}So, in your opinion this wasn't a case
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.56,0:27:36.48,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,本案與泛溢的警察腐敗現象無關\N{\rOriginal Text}of widespread police corruption?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.61,0:27:38.83,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,拜託 你沒看今天報紙嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Come on. You see the papers today?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.96,0:27:41.70,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,才沒什麼氾濫的腐敗現象\N{\rOriginal Text}There was no widespread corruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.00,0:27:45.18,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他們找到那個妓女了\N{\rOriginal Text}They found the prostitute.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.57,0:27:51.67,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我已經好久都沒想起那個晚上了\N{\rOriginal Text}Look, I haven't thought about that night for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.80,0:27:54.32,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我知道我就要死了\N{\rOriginal Text}I knew I was going to be murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.45,0:27:56.93,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,也知道沒人會在意\N{\rOriginal Text}and I knew no one would care.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.98,0:27:59.67,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所以我拚命反抗\N{\rOriginal Text}And so I just fought.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.80,0:28:03.81,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,因為上帝或者其他 你信仰的上蒼之力\N{\rOriginal Text}And because of God or whatever higher power you believe in,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.94,0:28:05.24,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我逃出來了\N{\rOriginal Text}I got away.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.37,0:28:07.46,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,其實本來逃不出來的\N{\rOriginal Text}And I shouldn't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.59,0:28:10.25,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,於是我改變了自己的生活\N{\rOriginal Text}And so I changed my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.38,0:28:12.34,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,戒毒了\N{\rOriginal Text}I got sober.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.47,0:28:15.34,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那是我做過最難的事\N{\rOriginal Text}Which was the hardest thing I ever did.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.47,0:28:17.95,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但我做到了\N{\rOriginal Text}But I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.08,0:28:20.35,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,後來我上了大學\N{\rOriginal Text}And I went to college and...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.48,0:28:23.48,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,過上了從沒想過的生活\N{\rOriginal Text}I have a life that I never imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.48,0:28:27.48,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但我家人不知道我的過去\N{\rOriginal Text}But, uh, my family doesn't know about my past.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.61,0:28:29.79,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我老公不知道孩子們 也不知道\N{\rOriginal Text}Not my husband, not my kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.92,0:28:31.88,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你可以在非公開法庭上作證\N{\rOriginal Text}Well, you could testify in closed court.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.01,0:28:33.79,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們只需要證明你在雷蒙德\N{\rOriginal Text}We just need to establish that you reported
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.92,0:28:36.10,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,入獄期間 報告過被人攻擊\N{\rOriginal Text}the attack while Raymond was in jail
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.23,0:28:38.15,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,能證明有人掩蓋真相就行\N{\rOriginal Text}to prove there was a cover-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.28,0:28:39.71,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不 會被曝出去的\N{\rOriginal Text}No, it will get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.84,0:28:41.76,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我孩子才十幾歲\N{\rOriginal Text}I have teenagers.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.89,0:28:44.41,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,抱歉 我不能去\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm sorry, I-I, I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.54,0:28:45.94,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們可以給你發傳票的\N{\rOriginal Text}We can subpoena you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.07,0:28:47.63,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不要 你們不明白\N{\rOriginal Text}No. No, you don't understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.76,0:28:48.98,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那會毀了我家庭的\N{\rOriginal Text}that will destroy my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.11,0:28:50.55,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,求你們了\N{\rOriginal Text}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.68,0:28:52.86,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,求求 你不知道我經歷過什麼\N{\rOriginal Text}Please, you don't know what I've been through.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.21,0:28:58.47,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,其實我們不能傳喚你的\N{\rOriginal Text}We can't actually subpoena you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.60,0:28:59.69,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,在這個階段\N{\rOriginal Text}To get you added
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.82,0:29:01.30,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,把你加入證人名單\N{\rOriginal Text}to the witness list this late,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.43,0:29:03.13,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們得提交一份\N{\rOriginal Text}we'd have to submit an affidavit
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.26,0:29:05.13,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你願意合作的宣誓書\N{\rOriginal Text}with your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.26,0:29:07.87,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我不會合作的\N{\rOriginal Text}Well, I won't give it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.13,0:29:10.22,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,抱歉\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.35,0:29:11.48,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我不能騙她\N{\rOriginal Text}I couldn't lie to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.61,0:29:12.92,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你也不用明確告知她\N{\rOriginal Text}Well, you also didn't have to give her
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.05,0:29:14.57,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,如何逃避作證嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}the road map on how to get out of testifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.70,0:29:16.92,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你說得對 我太久沒上班了\N{\rOriginal Text}You're right. And i-it's been a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.05,0:29:18.49,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所以 也許 也許什麼\N{\rOriginal Text}so maybe... Maybe what?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.62,0:29:20.01,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,也許 你不該回來上班\N{\rOriginal Text}Maybe you shouldn't have come back to work?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.14,0:29:21.76,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我同意\N{\rOriginal Text}I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.89,0:29:23.45,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所以在你提出區別對待和\N{\rOriginal Text}Which is why I didn't want you hired from the moment
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.58,0:29:26.67,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,年齡歧視的那一刻 我就不想雇你\N{\rOriginal Text}you brought up discriminatory practices and ageism,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.80,0:29:28.89,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你那就是濫用法律武器\N{\rOriginal Text}which is an offensive manipulation of a law
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.02,0:29:31.90,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,而那條法律 主要是為了防止從業者\N{\rOriginal Text}that was established primarily to keep workers from getting
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.03,0:29:34.94,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,被提前趕出公司 而你被拒絕的原因\N{\rOriginal Text}pushed out prematurely, whereas you getting blocked
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.07,0:29:37.60,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,則是因為你已經30年\N{\rOriginal Text}was likely because it has been 30 years
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.73,0:29:39.25,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,沒有從事法律工作了\N{\rOriginal Text}since you've practiced law.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.38,0:29:42.25,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,從最好的情況來看\N{\rOriginal Text}Which, best-case scenario,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.38,0:29:45.95,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你剛證明了這條法律的災難程度\N{\rOriginal Text}you just proved to be a recipe for disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.08,0:29:48.17,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,至於最壞的情況\N{\rOriginal Text}Worst-case scenario?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.30,0:29:50.13,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你給了那女人一條出路\N{\rOriginal Text}You gave that woman a way out
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.26,0:29:52.31,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,就因為你同情她\N{\rOriginal Text}because you felt sorry for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.44,0:29:53.48,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,因為你看到她\N{\rOriginal Text}Because you saw her
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.61,0:29:56.09,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,住在郊區\N{\rOriginal Text}living in suburbia
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.22,0:29:58.10,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,讓你想起了你自己\N{\rOriginal Text}and she reminded you of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.23,0:30:00.36,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但你知道嗎 那些讓你有共鳴的人\N{\rOriginal Text}But you know what? Those people who remind you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.49,0:30:02.36,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,相比於那些讓我有共鳴的人\N{\rOriginal Text}of yourself have generations of advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.49,0:30:04.62,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,享受了太多代的優勢了\N{\rOriginal Text}over the people who remind me of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.75,0:30:06.58,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你知道誰讓我想起自己了嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Do you know who I identify with?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.71,0:30:08.58,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,雷蒙德和他的家人\N{\rOriginal Text}Raymond and his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.71,0:30:11.20,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,而你剛剛把他們搞砸了\N{\rOriginal Text}Who you just screwed over.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.51,0:30:21.12,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,嘿 阿爾菲 是奶奶啊\N{\rOriginal Text}Hey, Alfie, it's Grammy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.25,0:30:25.51,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,抱歉啊 我又不能回家吃晚飯了\N{\rOriginal Text}Oh, I'm so sorry I won't be home for dinner again.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.12,0:30:28.56,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我聽起來怪怪的\N{\rOriginal Text}I sound weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.69,0:30:30.04,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,沒有啦 我沒事\N{\rOriginal Text}No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.17,0:30:31.87,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,只是很忙\N{\rOriginal Text}Just busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.87,0:30:37.05,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,有人叫我晚點再跟你聊哈\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm getting called in, so I'll talk to you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.70,0:30:41.31,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,想吃點咸的嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Something salty?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.36,0:30:43.36,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我不太會給人打氣\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm not one for pep talks,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.49,0:30:46.75,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但我是來支持\N{\rOriginal Text}but I am here to support
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.88,0:30:49.06,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,比利要給你的一些建議\N{\rOriginal Text}whatever Billy is about to say to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.19,0:30:50.97,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不用說\N{\rOriginal Text}There's no need to say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.11,0:30:54.54,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我錯了 太感情用事了\N{\rOriginal Text}I was wrong, I let my emotions get in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.67,0:30:57.20,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我年輕的時候絕不會這樣\N{\rOriginal Text}Something I'd never do when I was younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.33,0:30:59.72,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那時候我把事情分的很清楚\N{\rOriginal Text}Back then I kept things separate.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.77,0:31:02.81,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我只是不能\N{\rOriginal Text}I just can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.94,0:31:05.29,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,讓更多人失望了\N{\rOriginal Text}I can't let any more people down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.42,0:31:07.77,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,尤其是在我人生這個階段 我只是\N{\rOriginal Text}Not at this moment in my life, I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.56,0:31:10.99,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,做不到\N{\rOriginal Text}Can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.13,0:31:13.52,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,好吧 呃\N{\rOriginal Text}Okay. Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.65,0:31:15.13,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,是時候克服自我了\N{\rOriginal Text}Time to get over yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.26,0:31:17.91,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這很正常\N{\rOriginal Text}This is completely normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.05,0:31:20.18,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,大家都跑天台來哭 還記得嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}You know, we're on the crying patio, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.31,0:31:21.96,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但拜託\N{\rOriginal Text}But come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.09,0:31:23.18,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們跟你一起取得的成就\N{\rOriginal Text}I mean, we've accomplished more with you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.31,0:31:24.49,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,比這一年加起來都多\N{\rOriginal Text}than we have all year.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.62,0:31:26.49,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,倒也不是啦\N{\rOriginal Text}I mean, that's not entirely true.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.62,0:31:29.67,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,怎麼了 誇大其詞並不會讓人好受呀\N{\rOriginal Text}What? Hyperbole helps no one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.80,0:31:31.75,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但顯而易見 你還派的上用場\N{\rOriginal Text}But you've obviously been useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.89,0:31:33.28,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所以\N{\rOriginal Text}So...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.41,0:31:37.02,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,別再自怨自艾了 振作起來\N{\rOriginal Text}stop feeling bad for yourself and pull up whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.15,0:31:39.02,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,把這事解決掉\N{\rOriginal Text}granny panties you wear and fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.46,0:31:41.72,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,好嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.64,0:31:45.77,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,喬丹 你父親\N{\rOriginal Text}Jordan, after your father
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.90,0:31:50.60,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,被錯判入後 你生活發生了什麼變化\N{\rOriginal Text}was wrongfully imprisoned, how did your life change?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.73,0:31:53.73,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們沒了房子 我不得不轉學\N{\rOriginal Text}Well, we lost our housing. I had to switch schools.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.86,0:31:55.65,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所有人都知道我父親\N{\rOriginal Text}And everybody knew that my father
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.78,0:31:57.87,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,被判強姦和謀殺罪\N{\rOriginal Text}was convicted of rape and murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.00,0:32:00.26,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所以你猜 誰想跟我一起玩\N{\rOriginal Text}so you know who wanted to hang around me?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.39,0:32:02.96,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那些覺得這種事很酷的人\N{\rOriginal Text}Hmm? People who thought that was cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.09,0:32:04.48,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,怎麼會影響到你呢\N{\rOriginal Text}And how did that affect you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.61,0:32:05.53,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,怎麼會影響不到呢\N{\rOriginal Text}I mean, how didn't it affect me?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.66,0:32:07.79,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,能說得再具體些嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Can you be more specific?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.80,0:32:15.67,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這是你的機會 喬丹\N{\rOriginal Text}This is your chance, Jordan.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.41,0:32:23.68,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我現在37歲\N{\rOriginal Text}Well, I'm 37 years old now and...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.81,0:32:25.42,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,從沒談過戀愛\N{\rOriginal Text}I've never had a relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.55,0:32:28.55,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,為什麼 因為\N{\rOriginal Text}Why? Because
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.68,0:32:32.16,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,如果我認為我父親做出過\N{\rOriginal Text}if I thought my father was capable
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.29,0:32:34.73,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這種可怕的事 那我怎麼可能\N{\rOriginal Text}of this terrible thing, then how could I trust
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.86,0:32:36.65,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,信任別人\N{\rOriginal Text}anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.78,0:32:39.30,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但其實 他並沒有做\N{\rOriginal Text}But he wasn't capable of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.43,0:32:41.26,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,沒事的 有事\N{\rOriginal Text}It's okay. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.30,0:32:43.30,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,有事\N{\rOriginal Text}It's not okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.52,0:32:47.40,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,因為最糟糕的是\N{\rOriginal Text}Because the worst part is,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.53,0:32:50.75,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,最糟糕的是我和我爸\N{\rOriginal Text}the worst part is that me and my dad,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.88,0:32:53.01,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們曾經很親密 而我\N{\rOriginal Text}we used to be close, and I...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.45,0:32:57.45,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我不知道 怎樣才能找回那樣的時光\N{\rOriginal Text}I don't know how to get that back.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.58,0:33:00.71,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我找不回來了\N{\rOriginal Text}I can't get that back.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.02,0:33:07.59,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,沒有其他問題了 法官大人\N{\rOriginal Text}No further questions, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.94,0:33:10.72,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,就五分鐘\N{\rOriginal Text}Just five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.85,0:33:12.77,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,拜託了\N{\rOriginal Text}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.90,0:33:15.16,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我昨天幫了你\N{\rOriginal Text}I helped you yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.55,0:33:18.77,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,聽著 我知道這很重要\N{\rOriginal Text}Look, I understand what's at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.90,0:33:20.91,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我也理解你為什麼拒絕\N{\rOriginal Text}And I understand why you said no.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.04,0:33:22.60,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,比你想像的更理解\N{\rOriginal Text}More than you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.65,0:33:26.22,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我有過一個女兒\N{\rOriginal Text}I had a daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.26,0:33:30.70,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,在與毒品長期鬥爭後 她去世了\N{\rOriginal Text}And she died after a long battle with drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.74,0:33:35.70,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我每天都承受著失去她的痛苦\N{\rOriginal Text}And I carry the weight of that loss every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.83,0:33:38.27,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,通常我都能承受 對吧\N{\rOriginal Text}And usually I can handle it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.40,0:33:39.66,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但是\N{\rOriginal Text}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.84,0:33:43.54,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,有時 它總是出乎意料地\N{\rOriginal Text}...once in a while, and it's always unexpected...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.71,0:33:48.46,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,成為我唯一能看見的東西\N{\rOriginal Text}...it becomes the only thing in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.98,0:33:52.37,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,昨天又發生了這樣的事\N{\rOriginal Text}And yesterday that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.50,0:33:53.98,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,當你談到\N{\rOriginal Text}When you were talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.11,0:33:56.16,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你如何努力戒掉毒癮\N{\rOriginal Text}how hard you worked to get clean
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.29,0:33:58.99,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,以及你已經取得了多大的進步時候\N{\rOriginal Text}and how far you'd come...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.34,0:34:03.65,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我想到了 我該為我的女兒做些什麼\N{\rOriginal Text}...I thought about what I'd do for my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.91,0:34:09.83,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,答案是 我願意做任何事\N{\rOriginal Text}And the answer is anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.13,0:34:12.78,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我願傾盡一切\N{\rOriginal Text}Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.83,0:34:16.83,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但這事關雷蒙德·哈里斯和他的家人\N{\rOriginal Text}But this is about Raymond Harris and his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.96,0:34:19.62,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他們已經被毀了\N{\rOriginal Text}And they've been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.18,0:34:23.58,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但是 我不想毀了我的生活\N{\rOriginal Text}But I don't want to blow up my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.32,0:34:27.76,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,再說也不能保證他們就會相信我\N{\rOriginal Text}Plus there's no guarantee they'll even believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.89,0:34:30.11,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我是說 人們是不會關心妓女的\N{\rOriginal Text}I mean, people don't care about prostitutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.24,0:34:32.59,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,即使在那時 我也知道這是不會有結果的\N{\rOriginal Text}Even back then I knew it would go nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.72,0:34:34.89,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這就是為什麼我沒有\N{\rOriginal Text}That's why I didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.02,0:34:36.94,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,什麼\N{\rOriginal Text}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.38,0:34:39.72,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,卡琳 我以\N{\rOriginal Text}Carlin, I promise you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.86,0:34:42.21,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我女兒的名義 向你保證\N{\rOriginal Text}on my daughter's memory...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.47,0:34:45.86,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我不會背叛你\N{\rOriginal Text}...I will not betray you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.99,0:34:48.56,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但我需要知道 你都知道些什麼\N{\rOriginal Text}But I need to know what you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.43,0:34:52.87,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這家希臘餐館的老闆看到\N{\rOriginal Text}The owner of this Greek restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.00,0:34:54.61,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我把那傢伙打退了\N{\rOriginal Text}saw me fight the guy off.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.26,0:35:00.01,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,然後他陪我去了警察局\N{\rOriginal Text}And he walked me to the police station.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.79,0:35:03.57,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你好\N{\rOriginal Text}Hi there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.71,0:35:06.88,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我想知道克裏斯多老爹 還是這家店的老闆嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm wondering if Papa Cristo still owns this establishment?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.06,0:35:12.28,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,首先 我想說我很理解\N{\rOriginal Text}First, I want to say I appreciate
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.41,0:35:15.15,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,有個坐牢的父親 對你來說有多難\N{\rOriginal Text}how hard it must have been having a father in jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.28,0:35:18.76,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,雖然你之前經歷過他進監獄\N{\rOriginal Text}Though you had experienced his incarceration before,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.89,0:35:20.50,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,對吧 在你還小的時候\N{\rOriginal Text}am I right? Earlier in life?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.64,0:35:22.59,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,反對 我們能上前嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Objection! Can we approach?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.68,0:35:27.56,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這顯然帶有偏見\N{\rOriginal Text}That was clearly prejudicial.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.69,0:35:29.60,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,和暗示你的當事人 不出庭作證\N{\rOriginal Text}As prejudicial as suggesting your client
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.73,0:35:31.86,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,是因為他害怕公開演講一樣有偏見嗎 比那更糟\N{\rOriginal Text}isn't testifying because he's afraid of public speaking? Worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.99,0:35:33.52,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他讓陪審團把我的當事人\N{\rOriginal Text}He just made sure that the jury sees
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.65,0:35:35.87,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,當成罪犯 而不是受害者\N{\rOriginal Text}my client as a criminal instead of a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.00,0:35:37.65,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,夠了\N{\rOriginal Text}Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.78,0:35:39.48,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,反對有效 下次再發生這種事\N{\rOriginal Text}Objection sustained, and the next time this happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.61,0:35:41.09,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你倆都會面臨著無效審判\N{\rOriginal Text}you're both looking at a mistrial.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.84,0:35:54.58,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所以 我去了克裏斯多老爹餐廳\N{\rOriginal Text}And so I went to Papa Cristo's restaurant,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.71,0:35:56.41,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,信不信由你 他還在那裏\N{\rOriginal Text}and believe it or not, he's still there,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.54,0:35:58.50,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,頭腦還和以前一樣靈敏 而且他比我年紀都大\N{\rOriginal Text}still sharp as a tack, and he's older than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.63,0:36:00.07,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這太荒謬了\N{\rOriginal Text}This is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.20,0:36:01.37,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,案子都到這個階段了\N{\rOriginal Text}You cannot introduce a new witness
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.50,0:36:02.85,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你不能再加新證人進來\N{\rOriginal Text}this late in the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.98,0:36:04.55,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,更不用說 沒有妓女本人\N{\rOriginal Text}Not to mention, without the prostitute,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.68,0:36:06.46,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這不過是26年前的傳聞\N{\rOriginal Text}it's hearsay from 26 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.59,0:36:08.38,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這可以算是激情表述\N{\rOriginal Text}Which qualifies as an excited utterance.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.51,0:36:10.86,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,克裏斯多老爹告訴她 他目睹襲擊時\N{\rOriginal Text}Papa Cristo told her he was on the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.99,0:36:12.30,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,正在打電話\N{\rOriginal Text}when he witnessed the attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.43,0:36:13.43,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那又怎樣 他真的喊出看到的一切了嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}So what? He screamed to a friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.56,0:36:14.78,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,得了\N{\rOriginal Text}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.91,0:36:16.47,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,誰能清楚地為26年前的\N{\rOriginal Text}How can anyone testify with clarity
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.60,0:36:19.17,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,一段對話作證呢\N{\rOriginal Text}to a conversation that happened 26 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.30,0:36:21.74,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,啊 我明白了 但我問一下\N{\rOriginal Text}Ah. I got it. But just so I know
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.87,0:36:23.18,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,以防萬一\N{\rOriginal Text}for the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.31,0:36:25.83,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,如果那朋友錄下了電話內容 可以嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}if the friend taped the call, that'd be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.96,0:36:27.44,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,都這麼晚了\N{\rOriginal Text}I mean, you wouldn't argue
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.57,0:36:29.31,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你不會那個時候才反對 承認錄音的存在吧\N{\rOriginal Text}against admitting the tape this late?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.44,0:36:31.31,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那個朋友錄下了通話嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Did a friend tape the call?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.45,0:36:34.32,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不 但假設的話\N{\rOriginal Text}No. But hypothetically.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.45,0:36:36.93,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,假設那朋友錄下了電話\N{\rOriginal Text}Hypothetically, if a friend taped the call,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.06,0:36:37.97,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們會承認的\N{\rOriginal Text}we'd admit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.10,0:36:41.15,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,明白了 嗯 事情是這樣的\N{\rOriginal Text}Gotcha. Well, here's the thing--
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.28,0:36:44.28,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,克裏斯多老爹 沒有給朋友打電話\N{\rOriginal Text}Papa Cristo didn't call a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.41,0:36:45.98,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他報了警\N{\rOriginal Text}He called 911.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.11,0:36:48.51,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所以 我們申請了錄音\N{\rOriginal Text}So we requested the audio recording,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.64,0:36:50.20,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,錄音不在警察局\N{\rOriginal Text}which wasn't at the police station,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.33,0:36:53.95,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但幸運的是 在州服務器上有通話備份\N{\rOriginal Text}but luckily it was backed up on the state's server,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.08,0:36:56.17,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所以\N{\rOriginal Text}so...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.30,0:36:58.08,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們要把它作為證據嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}we'll go ahead and admit that into evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.34,0:37:01.78,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,帶著你的祝福呈上\N{\rOriginal Text}With your blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.35,0:37:08.53,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,是的 嘿 我剛看到一個女孩 從一個傢伙的車裏逃出來\N{\rOriginal Text}PAPA CRISTO [on recording]: Yeah, hey, I just saw some girl escape this guy's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.66,0:37:11.09,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,等一下 親愛的 我在報警呢\N{\rOriginal Text}Hang on, honey, I'm on with 911!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.22,0:37:13.62,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,她脖子上圍著長筒襪什麼的 然後\N{\rOriginal Text}She's got like a stocking or something around her neck and...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.75,0:37:15.36,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,噢 她說她沒事\N{\rOriginal Text}Oh, she says she's okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.49,0:37:18.14,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但我還是要送她去警局\N{\rOriginal Text}but I'm gonna walk her down to the station, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.27,0:37:19.93,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,弗格森警探\N{\rOriginal Text}Detective Ferguson,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.06,0:37:21.23,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,根據你的經驗\N{\rOriginal Text}using your metrics,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.36,0:37:23.06,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,以最可信的情況來說\N{\rOriginal Text}what is the most believable scenario
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.19,0:37:25.85,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,為什麼這個電話 沒有記錄在你的轄區呢\N{\rOriginal Text}for why this call was not logged in your precinct?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.29,0:37:31.64,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,是有人把記錄刪掉了\N{\rOriginal Text}Someone got rid of the record.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.77,0:37:32.98,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,意思是 有人為了給我的委託人定罪\N{\rOriginal Text}Meaning they buried the evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.12,0:37:35.12,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,而隱藏了證據\N{\rOriginal Text}in order to convict my client?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.34,0:37:37.21,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rOriginal Text}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.56,0:37:46.61,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,陪審團作出一致裁決了嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Has the jury reached a verdict?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.74,0:37:48.09,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,是的 法官大人\N{\rOriginal Text}Yes, we have, Your Honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.79,0:37:58.97,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,紐約州對雷蒙德·哈里斯有補償義務嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Does the State of New York owe a duty to Raymond Harris?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.10,0:38:00.93,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,答案是肯定的\N{\rOriginal Text}The answer is yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.06,0:38:02.67,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,請說明 你們認定的應當\N{\rOriginal Text}Please state the total amount of money
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.80,0:38:05.06,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,賠償原告雷蒙德·哈里斯的總金額\N{\rOriginal Text}that you would compensate the plaintiff Raymond Harris.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.67,0:38:09.85,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,2000萬美元\N{\rOriginal Text}$20 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.86,0:38:19.77,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你剛才說的那些\N{\rOriginal Text}What you said up there--
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.90,0:38:21.60,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們要重建我們的關係\N{\rOriginal Text}we're gonna build back our relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.73,0:38:24.17,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我愛你\N{\rOriginal Text}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.09,0:38:33.65,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,很抱歉\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.78,0:38:36.00,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我之前忽略了客戶的最大利益\N{\rOriginal Text}for losing sight of the client's best interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.13,0:38:37.35,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這種情況不會再發生了\N{\rOriginal Text}Won't happen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.92,0:38:41.84,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我希望你能支持我 爭取永久職位\N{\rOriginal Text}And I hope you'll support my bid for permanent employment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.97,0:38:43.58,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你給我爭取來感恩節週末了嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Did you get me Thanksgiving weekend?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.71,0:38:44.84,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,沒有\N{\rOriginal Text}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.28,0:38:48.84,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但話說回來 我猜你不想要那個週末\N{\rOriginal Text}But then again, I'm guessing you didn't want the weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.97,0:38:50.80,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,因為如果你想要\N{\rOriginal Text}Because if you did,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.93,0:38:54.15,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你就不會引導你前夫離開了\N{\rOriginal Text}you wouldn't have baited your ex-husband into going away.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.20,0:38:56.46,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,就像你一開始引導\N{\rOriginal Text}Same way you baited me
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.59,0:38:59.72,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我對這個案子發表的意見一樣\N{\rOriginal Text}into giving my opinion on the case early on.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.85,0:39:03.16,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所以 我想知道你為什麼想讓他離開紐約\N{\rOriginal Text}Which makes me wonder why you want him out of the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.25,0:39:06.64,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但也許我想多了\N{\rOriginal Text}But maybe I'm overthinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.77,0:39:10.21,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,也許不是因為你在和別人約會\N{\rOriginal Text}Maybe it's not that you're dating someone new,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.34,0:39:12.35,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,某個他不喜歡的人\N{\rOriginal Text}someone he'd be unhappy about.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.61,0:39:16.13,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,也許只是我想多了\N{\rOriginal Text}That's just where my paranoid mind went.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.26,0:39:18.00,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rOriginal Text}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.09,0:39:20.09,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你的推薦信通過審查了\N{\rOriginal Text}Your references checked out
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.22,0:39:22.14,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你很有幫助\N{\rOriginal Text}and you were useful,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.27,0:39:23.09,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,所以給你分配了\N{\rOriginal Text}so you've been assigned
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.23,0:39:25.45,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,一間辦公室\N{\rOriginal Text}an office.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.58,0:39:27.88,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我期待著再次與你合作\N{\rOriginal Text}And I look forward to working with you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.94,0:39:39.50,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,請把它關掉\N{\rOriginal Text}Please turn that off.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.63,0:39:41.20,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不行\N{\rOriginal Text}No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.33,0:39:44.07,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我要看幾集 安吉拉·蘭斯伯裏\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm gonna watch a few episodes, Angela Lansbury.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.20,0:39:45.38,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,等我們喝完酒看 是嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}After we drink, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.51,0:39:46.64,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你來嗎 瑪蒂\N{\rOriginal Text}You coming, Matty?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.77,0:39:48.69,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,哦 要是我再年輕40歲\N{\rOriginal Text}Oh, if only I was 40 years younger
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.82,0:39:50.03,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,而且家裏沒有一個搗亂的孫子就好了\N{\rOriginal Text}and didn't have a surly grandson at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.17,0:39:51.73,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,明天見\N{\rOriginal Text}I'll see you two tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.86,0:39:52.86,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我得去趕公交了\N{\rOriginal Text}I got to catch my bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.99,0:39:54.52,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,好吧 晚安\N{\rOriginal Text}All right, good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.50,0:40:18.02,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,就一站嗎 對\N{\rOriginal Text}Just the one stop? Just the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.20,0:40:23.50,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,晚上好 馬庫斯\N{\rOriginal Text}Good evening, Marcus.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.63,0:40:25.37,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,晚上好 金斯頓夫人\N{\rOriginal Text}Good evening, Mrs. Kingston.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.68,0:40:27.94,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,嗯 你看當女人變老時\N{\rOriginal Text}Well, you see there's this funny thing
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.07,0:40:29.38,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,會發生一件有趣的事情\N{\rOriginal Text}that happens when women age.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.42,0:40:32.16,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我們變得近乎隱形\N{\rOriginal Text}We become damn near invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.29,0:40:34.34,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,沒人會警惕我們的存在\N{\rOriginal Text}Nobody sees us coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.39,0:40:44.22,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,人生中總有那麼一段時間\N{\rOriginal Text}There's a time in life when you make decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.35,0:40:46.18,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你會根據自己的想法做決定\N{\rOriginal Text}based on what you think is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.31,0:40:48.53,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但現在我又窮又困頓\N{\rOriginal Text}But now I'm bitter and broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.66,0:40:51.62,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,她來了 我們的征戰大將軍\N{\rOriginal Text}There she is. Our conquering hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.88,0:40:55.19,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,如果你知道 我在工作時是怎麼說你的\N{\rOriginal Text}Well, you'd been a lot less cheery if you knew
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.32,0:40:56.75,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你就不會這麼高興了\N{\rOriginal Text}how I talked about you at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.88,0:40:58.10,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,賭博 出軌\N{\rOriginal Text}Gambling, cheating...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.23,0:41:00.41,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,還說你死了 嗯\N{\rOriginal Text}not to mention dead. Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.54,0:41:03.93,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,瑪德琳·馬特洛克可以褻瀆關於我的假記憶\N{\rOriginal Text}Madeline Matlock can desecrate my false memory
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.07,0:41:06.76,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,只要瑪德琳·金斯頓還愛我就行\N{\rOriginal Text}as long as Madeline Kingston loves me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.89,0:41:08.42,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我愛你 嗯\N{\rOriginal Text}I do. Aw.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.55,0:41:09.59,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,如果再讓我吃一個這玩意兒\N{\rOriginal Text}And if I have to eat one more of these,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.72,0:41:11.07,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我就要殺人了\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm gonna kill somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.99,0:41:14.68,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,但無辜的老太太是真喜歡買 姥姥\N{\rOriginal Text}But they really sell harmless old lady. -Grammy!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.82,0:41:16.73,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,阿爾菲\N{\rOriginal Text}Oh! Alfie.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.86,0:41:18.60,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,親愛的\N{\rOriginal Text}Oh, sweetheart, oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.73,0:41:20.12,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我在帶孫子\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm raising my grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.26,0:41:23.61,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,不用向我徵求任何意見 他討厭我\N{\rOriginal Text}Don't ask me for any advice. He loathes me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.65,0:41:26.48,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,看到了嗎 你昨晚白擔心了一場\N{\rOriginal Text}See? You were upset for nothing last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.61,0:41:27.48,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你贏了\N{\rOriginal Text}You won.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.61,0:41:28.87,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,嗯 是奧林匹亞贏了\N{\rOriginal Text}Well, Olympia won.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.00,0:41:30.57,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我已經十年沒做律師了\N{\rOriginal Text}I haven't practiced law in ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.70,0:41:32.31,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,至少我沒有毀了這案子\N{\rOriginal Text}At least I didn't ruin it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.44,0:41:33.70,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,就像《馬特洛克》的情節一樣\N{\rOriginal Text}It's just like on Matlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.83,0:41:35.05,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,他們差點就輸了 但後來又贏了\N{\rOriginal Text}They almost lose, but then they win.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.18,0:41:36.92,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我說的對嗎 你說得對\N{\rOriginal Text}Was I right? You were right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.05,0:41:38.36,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,完美的名字嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Perfect name?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.49,0:41:41.84,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,很適合瑪蒂 讓我們想起了媽媽\N{\rOriginal Text}Fits with Matty, reminds us of Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.97,0:41:46.24,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我能清楚地想起她 死死地盯著電視\N{\rOriginal Text}I can see her clear as day, glued to the television,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.37,0:41:48.02,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,跟大家說 她在學做律師\N{\rOriginal Text}telling everybody she was learning
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.15,0:41:50.02,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,就像她媽媽一樣\N{\rOriginal Text}to be a lawyer, just like her mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.15,0:41:52.07,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我想你得到那份工作了吧\N{\rOriginal Text}I assume you got the job?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.20,0:41:54.07,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,因為我創建的那個領英賬號 有大量的瀏覽\N{\rOriginal Text}Because there's been traffic to the LinkedIn I made,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.20,0:41:56.51,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,而且我把人力資源背景調查 轉給了姥爺\N{\rOriginal Text}plus I rerouted an HR reference check to Pops.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.64,0:41:58.42,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我推薦信寫得很公允\N{\rOriginal Text}Now, I was fair if extremely partial.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.55,0:42:01.08,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,是的 我正式成為了\N{\rOriginal Text}Yes, I'm officially a new employee
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.21,0:42:02.43,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,雅各布森·摩爾公司的新員工\N{\rOriginal Text}of Jacobson Moore.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.56,0:42:04.73,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那你什麼時候 代理處理藥品案件\N{\rOriginal Text}So, when do you get to work on drug cases?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.87,0:42:07.69,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你專攻製藥方面 對嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}You specialize in pharmaceuticals, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.82,0:42:09.78,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,那才是我該去的地方\N{\rOriginal Text}That's where I need to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.91,0:42:13.31,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我得先建立一點信任\N{\rOriginal Text}Well, I have to build up a little trust first.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.44,0:42:15.18,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,聽著 我要做些筆記\N{\rOriginal Text}Listen, I'm gonna make a few notes,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.31,0:42:17.53,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你去洗洗準備吃飯吧 好嗎 阿爾菲\N{\rOriginal Text}so why don't you go get washed up for dinner, okay, Alfie?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.72,0:42:34.02,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,親愛的 你看起來很累\N{\rOriginal Text}You look tired, darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.29,0:42:37.55,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,你確定你可以嗎\N{\rOriginal Text}Are you sure you can do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.68,0:42:40.51,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我必須可以 埃德溫\N{\rOriginal Text}I have to, Edwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.64,0:42:42.90,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,這三人中有一人隱藏了\N{\rOriginal Text}One of those three hid documents
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.03,0:42:45.17,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,可以早十年將阿片類藥物\N{\rOriginal Text}that could have taken opioids off the market
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.30,0:42:46.91,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,撤出市場的文件\N{\rOriginal Text}ten years earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.30,0:42:50.74,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,想想那會挽救多少生命\N{\rOriginal Text}Think of how many lives that could have saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.70,0:42:55.61,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,包括我們的女兒\N{\rOriginal Text}Including our daughter's.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.74,0:42:58.40,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我想過 我該為我女兒做些什麼\N{\rOriginal Text}I thought about what I'd do for my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.53,0:43:02.36,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,答案是 我願意做任何事\N{\rOriginal Text}And the answer is anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.49,0:43:04.01,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我願傾盡一切\N{\rOriginal Text}Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.84,0:43:08.71,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,聽以我要查出 是誰在什麼時候 知道了什麼\N{\rOriginal Text}So I'm gonna figure out who knew what, when.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.19,0:43:12.28,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,然後呢\N{\rOriginal Text}And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.37,0:43:15.94,Translated Text,,0,0,0,,我要把那人送進監獄\N{\rOriginal Text}I'm gonna put them in jail.


